================================================================
PRACTICAL NO. 9 - SEND MAIL, KEYBOARD EVENTS & EXCEPTION HANDLING
================================================================

PRE-REQUISITES:
- UiPath Studio installed
- UiPath.Mail.Activities installed (Manage Packages → search Mail → Install)
- A Gmail account (with App Password if 2FA is on)
- Chrome browser with UiPath Extension

================================================================
PRACTICAL 9(a) - Automate the Process of Sending an Email
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Easy-Medium

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will create a UiPath workflow that automatically sends an email
using Gmail's SMTP server.

--- STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS ---

Step 1: Set up Gmail App Password (if your Gmail has 2-Step Verification ON):
  - Go to: https://myaccount.google.com
  - Click Security → 2-Step Verification → scroll down → App Passwords
  - Select App: Mail  |  Device: Windows Computer
  - Click Generate → copy the 16-character password shown.
  - Use THIS password in UiPath, not your regular Gmail password.

Step 2: Open UiPath Studio → New Project.
  - Name it: Practical_9a_SendMail
  - Click Create

Step 3: Install Mail Activities (if not already):
  - Manage Packages → search "UiPath.Mail.Activities" → Install → Save

Step 4: From the Activities panel, search for "Send SMTP Mail Message"
        and drag it into the Main sequence.

Step 5: Fill in the activity properties (click on the activity to see them 
        on the right side):

  TO:         "recipient@gmail.com"   ← put your own email to test
  SUBJECT:    "Test Email from UiPath"
  BODY:       "Hello! This email was automatically sent by UiPath RPA."
  
  SMTP Settings (expand the SMTP section):
  HOST:       "smtp.gmail.com"
  PORT:       587
  EnableSSL:  True (check the checkbox)
  
  USERNAME:   "yourgmail@gmail.com"
  PASSWORD:   (see Step 6 below for how to enter securely)

Step 6: To handle password securely:
  - Before the Send SMTP activity, drag an "Assign" activity.
  - Left side (variable name): securePass  (Type: SecureString)
  - Right side (value): 
      New System.Net.NetworkCredential("", "your_app_password_here").SecurePassword
  - In the Send SMTP activity → Password field: securePass

Step 7: (Optional) Add an attachment:
  - In Send SMTP Mail Message → Attachments field:
  - Type: New List(Of String) From {"C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\sample.pdf"}
  - This attaches a file from your Desktop.

Step 8: Drag a "Message Box" AFTER the Send SMTP activity.
  - Text: "Email sent successfully!"

Step 9: Run (F5).
  - Wait a few seconds.
  - Check your email inbox — the email should arrive.
  - The Message Box "Email sent successfully!" will also appear.

COMMON ERRORS AND FIXES:
  Error: "5.7.8 Username and Password not accepted"
  Fix:   Use App Password (not normal Gmail password). Or enable 
         "Less secure app access" in Google Account settings.

  Error: "Connection refused" or timeout
  Fix:   Check port (587 for TLS, 465 for SSL) and EnableSSL setting.

